Interface SideEffectPipe<S,T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<S>, Iterator<S>, Pipe<S,S>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SideEffectPipe.GreedySideEffectPipe<S,T>, SideEffectPipe.LazySideEffectPipe<S,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregatePipe, CountPipe, GroupByPipe, GroupByReducePipe, GroupCountFunctionPipe, GroupCountPipe, LinkPipe, OptionalPipe, StorePipe, TablePipe, TreePipe

    public interface SideEffectPipe<S,T>
extends Pipe<S,S>
    A SideEffectPipe will produce a side effect which can be retrieved by the getSideEffect() method.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)
